Clean and mindful. It's a family affair, and they're very thoughtful about what they provide to customers. Not anything like a swanky chinese food restaurant, it's a true carryout, with just a few small cafeteria tables for those who might choose to sit and eat. But it's much cleaner and organized than many of your typical DC Chinese food carryout spots. The food is great too, even the American dishes like fried chicken and steak & cheese sandwiches. I definitely recommend.
